						               													<description>Players attempt to score a bingo on their individual &amp;ldquo;Parts of Speech&amp;rdquo; card. A player rolls the die and selects a card from their opponent&amp;rsquo;s hand. The number rolled determines which word to use on the chosen card for construction of a sentence later in the game. The player must identify the correct part of speech shared by all words on the card. If successful, they add the card to their hand and mark off the appropriate space on their bingo board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are Dapper cards in the deck which allow the scoring of one additional point when declaring bingo and constructing a sentence, as well as Zapper cards which prevent a player from declaring bingo as long as they are in possession of that card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once a players declares bingo, they must construct a sentence from the cards they have in their hand with the words designated by their previous rolls. A point is scored for each word successfully used. The first player to 21 points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
